						<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4d00834 elementor-widget__width-initial exad-sticky-section-no exad-glass-effect-no elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="4d00834" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
									<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-3278" src="https://ultacademy.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/logo.jpg" alt="" width="143" height="70" srcset="https://ultacademy.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/logo.jpg 280w, https://ultacademy.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/logo-18x9.jpg 18w" sizes="(max-width: 143px) 100vw, 143px" /></p><p><strong>Ukrainian Mind Bridge</strong></p><p>Ukrainian<i> </i>Mind Bridge (UMB) is a Ukrainian organization whose activities are aimed at uniting talented and hard-working schoolchildren who want to participate in the Olympiads, but are unable to prepare for them due to the lack of appropriate resources. The goal of UMB is to enable knowledge exchange and provide support to pupils interested in growing their knowledge of specific subjects and participating in Olympiads. Please see<a href="http://umb.org.ua"> the website of the initiative</a>.</p>								</div>
