															<span class="elementor-accordion-icon-closed"><svg class="e-font-icon-svg e-fas-angle-down" viewBox="0 0 320 512" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M143 352.3L7 216.3c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l22.6-22.6c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l96.4 96.4 96.4-96.4c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l22.6 22.6c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-136 136c-9.2 9.4-24.4 9.4-33.8 0z"></path></svg></span>
								<span class="elementor-accordion-icon-opened"><svg class="e-font-icon-svg e-fas-chevron-up" viewBox="0 0 448 512" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M240.971 130.524l194.343 194.343c9.373 9.373 9.373 24.569 0 33.941l-22.667 22.667c-9.357 9.357-24.522 9.375-33.901.04L224 227.495 69.255 381.516c-9.379 9.335-24.544 9.317-33.901-.04l-22.667-22.667c-9.373-9.373-9.373-24.569 0-33.941L207.03 130.525c9.372-9.373 24.568-9.373 33.941-.001z"></path></svg></span>
														</span>
												<a class="elementor-accordion-title" tabindex="0">Yaryna Holoshchuk</a>
					</div>
					<div id="elementor-tab-content-1261" class="elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix" data-tab="1" role="region" aria-labelledby="elementor-tab-title-1261"><p>Yaryna was involved in teams working on UAThon, a platform fostering innovation through hackathons; AIBI, an AI recruitment assistant; and Stezhkamy, an app gamifying walking while promoting Ukrainian culture. She attended ULTA Summer Program I in Barcelona, Spain, and Summer Program II in Warsaw, Poland, both led by MIT mentors. Yaryna also studied &#8220;18.06 Linear Algebra,&#8221; an MIT course taught and proctored by MIT students.</p></div>
